               <msContents>
                  <summary>Psalter  F. 1: Opening prayer from the Psalter of the Virgin. F<locus target="#1r">fols. 1r, </locus>-144v: 151 Psalms of David. The midpoint of the Psalms (<locus target="#57v">57v, </locus>) is marked with a small text in the right margin, ዝየ መን[ፈቁ]. Psalm 151 is the short version.  The fourth biblical cantile is "about the Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophetess."  The Song of Songs is in the common edition. The Praises of Mary begins on Monday. Varia: F i r: Asmat prayer for protection from strong drink. <locus target="#144v">144v</locus>, column 2: An exhortation to the reading of the Psalms (because they are about Jesus) and Praises of Mary (because they are about Mary). To not do so is very bad.  Written in a secondary hand.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <textLang/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
